// Bad: pre-0.8 compiler, no automatic overflow checks
// pragma solidity ^0.6.12;

// Good: upgrade to a current 0.8.x release and pin it
pragma solidity 0.8.24;

// Migration notes when moving to 0.8.x:
// 1. SafeMath is no longer needed: arithmetic reverts on overflow by default.
//    Remove "using SafeMath for uint256;" and .add/.sub/.mul calls.
// 2. Type conversions must be explicit, e.g. uint8(uint256(x)) instead of uint8(x)
//    when narrowing across sizes and signedness.
// 3. Replace deprecated constructs (now, throw, var) with their modern equivalents.
// 4. Re-run the full test suite: reverts that were silent wraps before will now surface.
